description:
Sergeant Jed Patterson had been a coal-miner before the war until a pit accident had nearly cost him his life.
He was left with a fear of going underground, but it was a fear he had to conquer - in order to battle with a secret army of German S.S. troops lurking where he least wanted to fight!
name: Underground Army

description: The Gods Walk the Earth! In ancient times, the Celestials, a race of cosmic giants, came to Earth and created a race of powerful immortal beings: The Eternals! For a time, primitive man worshipped them as gods, but eventually they disappeared. Now, they have returned! One of the Celestials now towers over Golden Gate Park, standing in judgement over the Earth, but does he bring the end of the world? Following up on Neil Gaiman's best-selling series (and a recent appearance in the Incredible Hercules), join writers Charles and Daniel Knauf as Jack Kirby's Eternals return to walk among us! Collecting ETERNALS #1-6 and ANNUAL.
name: Eternals: To Slay a God

A Clash Between Buddha and Evil

description: The legendary classic issues of Ben Edlund's The Tick, as originally published in 1986, but now in color! Destiny calls as The Tick arrives in The City to commence his superhero career! Thus begins a twice-a-month reprinting of the original 12-issue Edlund Tick, in a gorgeous new color format, and is followed by issue #2, in which The Tick, armed with new secret identity (and a fancy new tie), lands a job at a great metropolitan newspaper as a crossword puzzle editor! Digitally remastered and recolored to bring an intensity of color you haven't ever seen before!
